y part is that updating the existing configmap requires restarting those pods to pick up the changes.\n\nActually, I'm realizing there's a cleaner approach: leave the existing nodes without a zone attribute and only assign `node.attr.zone: secondary` to the new nodes. Then I can use `index.routing.allocation.require.zone: secondary` on the `app-data` index to force all its shards onto the new nodes, which satisfies the verification requirements without needing to restart the existing cluster.\n\nSo the plan is to create a new StatefulSet for the data nodes with the secondary zone attribute, configure them to join the cluster using the existing nodes as seed hosts, and ensure they can access the same TLS certificates. Then I'll create the `app-data` index with the appropriate routing constraint. I need to configure the ConfigMap with cluster settings, node roles set to data-only, and the zone attribute, then point the seed hosts to the existing master nodes. I'll also create a separate headless service for the new StatefulSet and deploy it with 2 replicas. But I should verify the TLS certificate covers the new pod hostnames before proceeding, since the existing setup uses a shared secret for both HTTP and transport encryption.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":911,"cache_read_input_tokens":32798,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":911},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f19d5cb-adf2-400c-a2cf-a8445ed51696","uuid":"b61eef51-3685-49b7-ae1d-e064fdbc6351","request_id":"req_011Cc6nNvbB33HRWTi6bCTe9"}
